    "description": "<div class='descriptionContainer'>    <div class='pdpRow'>        <div class='note-text'>            This product is not compatible with the ND3 Miata        </div>        <div class='productText'>            <h3>                A one-of-a-kind tachometer            </h3>            <p>                For several years CravenSpeed has been focused on designing high quality parts to further refine the                interior of the ND MX-5 Miata. This billet alluminum tachometer dial is one of the most impactful parts                we have created for the car. It has been precisely machined on every single face to achieve a level of                detail that will impress even non-enthusiast passengers. You won't find a more unique product for your                ND Miata on the market, and this one promises to put a smile on your face every time you drive it.            </p>        </div>        <div class='productGraphic'>            <img src='https://www.cravenspeed.com/product_images/uploaded_images/red-edition-tach-dial-drawing.jpg' />        </div>    </div>    <div class='pdpRow'>        <div class='productGraphic'>            <img                src='https://www.cravenspeed.com/product_images/uploaded_images/red-edition-tach-dial-left-quarter-view.jpg' />        </div>        <div class='productText'>            <h3>                A red hot commodity            </h3>            <p>                In 2018, after interest in the product was shown on a                <a class='descriptionLink' href='https://forum.miata.net/vb/showthread.php?t=662991' target='_blank'>                    miata.net                </a>                forum post, we made our first 11 billet tachometer dials. We knew that we wouldn't be able to produce                such a complicated piece at a low price point, so instead we decided to go all out with the design and                release a limited run of 11 custom dials. All 11 sold within 4 hours.            </p>            <h3>                No mass production here            </h3>            <p>                Each dial is carefully machined in house at CravenSpeed's Portland, OR headquarters from 6061 Aluminum.                <b>                    This version will fit all 2019-2023 ND2 Miatas, as the redline has been raised for the new cars. It                    will                    <strong>                        not                    </strong>                    fit ND1 MX-5 Miatas of model years 2016, 2017, and 2018, including the RF hardtop convertible. It                    will not fit 2024+ ND3 Miatas.                </b>                Installation of the dial is very easy, and should only take a first timer around 15 minutes using very                basic hand tools.            </p>        </div>    </div></div>",
